# React + MUI Component Patterns

## Component Structure

```tsx
import Box from '@mui/material/Box'
import Typography from '@mui/material/Typography'
import type { SomeType } from '../../types'

interface MyComponentProps {
  data: SomeType
  optional?: boolean
}

export default function MyComponent({ data, optional = false }: MyComponentProps) {
  return (
    <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: 1 }}>
      <Typography variant="subtitle1" sx={{ fontWeight: 600 }}>
        {data.title}
      </Typography>
    </Box>
  )
}
```

## Key Patterns

- Default export, PascalCase filename matching component name
- MUI imports: one per line from specific paths (`@mui/material/Box`, not `@mui/material`)
- Props interface inline, named `{ComponentName}Props`
- Styling exclusively via `sx` prop
- Heavy components (Recharts): wrap in `React.lazy()` + `<Suspense>`
- ContentBlock rendering: use if-chain on `block.type` (discriminated union), see `FactSection.tsx`
- Mobile-first: touch targets ≥ 48px, responsive via MUI breakpoints
